What are the id generators available in Jpa ap?
Jpa api has provided 4 id generators
1. AUTO = similar to native, it automatically switches between IDENTITY and SEQUENCE based on database we are using
2. IDENTITY = works with databases that supports auto increment or identity column types
3. SEQUENCE = generates the id based on oracle sequence
4. TABLE = generates the ids based on the database table.
  
  
class Customer {}
class Product {}

table(name="hibernate_unique_key", pkColumnName="pk_column_nm", pkColumnNameValue="companyNo", pkColumnValueName="pk_column_value")
class Company {
  int companyNo;
}

hibernate_unique_key (table)
pk_column_nm  pk_column_value
customer_no             12
product_no              101
  
unique_keys
pkName   pkValue
bill     1

select pk_column_value from hibernate_unique_key where pk_column_nm = 'companyNo'
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@Entity
@Table(name="bill")  
@SequenceGenerator(name="bill_gen", sequenceName="bill_no_sequence", allocationSize=1)
@TableGenerator(name="bill_tbl_gen", table="unique_keys", pkColumnName="pkName", valueColumnName="pkValue", pkColumnValue="bill", initialValue=1, allocationSize=1)  
class Bill {
  @Id
  @Column(name="bill_no")
  
  /*@GeneratedValue(strategy=GenerationType.SEQUENCE, generator="bill_gen")*/
  @GeneratedValue(strategy=GenerationType.TABLE, generator="bill_tbl_gen")
  int billNo;
  
  @Column(name="customer_nm")
  String customerName;
  @Column(name="bill_dt")
  Date billDate;
  String description;
  double amount;
  //accessors
  // equals and hashcode  
}
  
  
@GeneratedValue = means the value for this column is generated by someone
strategy = indicates the type of id generation
GenerationType = ENUM, can carry 4 values
  .AUTO
  .SEQUENCE
  .IDENTITY
  .TABLE
depends on the strategy assign one of the value

@GeneratedValue(strategy=GenerationType.SEQUENCE) = if we dont specify any sequenceName the default sequenceName it uses is hibernate_sequence, so that across the tables id is not going to be sequential
















  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  